@node sect0 "Name"
samformat - format a Sam diskette 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}samformat@{ub} [ @{b}-diskfile @{ub}@{i}file@{ui} ] 
@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
On a Sun SPARCstation, this program configures the floppy disk device and formats the floppy disk to the usual format of 80 cylinders of 10 sectors per side.  The name of the device is usually /dev/rfd0 but may be changed by setting the environment variable SAMDISKFILE to the name of a file or supplying the @{b}-diskfile @{ub}@{i}file@{ui} flag.  If used this flag must be written first on the command line.  It may be abbreviated to @{b}-disk @{ub}@{i}file@{ui}@{b}.@{ub} If the named device is a regular file (or a file which does not exist) then @{b}samformat@{ub} will create a new disk image file with the given name, wiping any current contents of the file, instead of formatting a floppy disk. The program will not format floppies on non-Sun workstations, but it can still be used to create disk image files. 

The diskette or image when formatted will be completely empty.  To give it a disk label or to set the number of directory tracks, use the @{b}samlabel@{ub} command.  


@endnode

@node sect3 "See Also"
samtools(1), samlabel(1)  
@endnode
